President Trump attended the groundbreaking ceremony for a new Foxconn plant in Wisconsin. The plant, which is one of the largest in the world, is expected to create more than 13,000 jobs. Trump praised Foxconn Chairman Terry Gou and thanked him for investing in Wisconsin and the United States. He also mentioned the recent successes of his administration, such as job creation, tax cuts, and deregulation. Trump highlighted the importance of fair and reciprocal trade and mentioned his efforts to renegotiate trade deals with countries like China and the European Union. He also discussed his plans to nominate a new Supreme Court justice to replace Justice Kennedy. Trump emphasized the economic benefits of the new Foxconn plant and mentioned some of the workers who will benefit from the job opportunities it creates. He concluded by expressing his confidence in the economic future of the United States.